The RPM packages of Flint make it easy to install and uninstall Flint on
an RPM-flavor distribution such as CentOS and RHEL.
They consist of:
  flint-(version)-(release).(dist).(arch).rpm
where (version) is the version string of Flint,
(release) is the release number of the package, and
(arch) is either "x86" or "x86_64".
